          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Explore Tbilisi's enchanting Old Town, where centuries of architectural heritage blend seamlessly with modern creative energy. Founded in 458 AD at the crossroads of Europe and Asia, the Georgian capital showcases an extraordinary mix of medieval fortresses, ornate churches, Soviet-era monuments, and contemporary art installations. Wander through narrow cobblestone streets where ancient stone walls meet colorful balconies adorned with intricate wooden carvings.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Ascend to the Narikala Fortress via the scenic cable car for panoramic views spanning the entire city and the winding Mtkvari River below. This ancient citadel dates back to the 4th century and has witnessed countless invasions and reconstructions throughout Georgia's turbulent history. The fortress ramparts offer exceptional vantage points for photography, especially during golden hour when the city glows beneath the Caucasus foothills.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Discover the famous Dry Bridge Market, a sprawling open-air bazaar where vendors display Soviet memorabilia, antique jewelry, traditional crafts, and curious treasures from decades past. This vibrant gathering place perfectly captures Tbilisi's eclectic spirit and offers fascinating insights into Georgian culture and history.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            },
            {
              "text": "Rejuvenate in the historic sulfur baths of Abanotubani, the bathhouse district where natural hot springs have drawn visitors for centuries. The distinctive domed brick structures house therapeutic mineral waters that remain a cherished Georgian tradition. Stroll through the adjacent botanical garden for peaceful walking paths amid lush vegetation.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
