              "Jvari Monastery",
              "Old Town Mtskheta",
              "Mtkvari Aragvi Rivers Confluence"
            ]
          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Visit Mtskheta, designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site and revered as Georgia's sacred city by the Orthodox Church. This ancient settlement served as the nation's capital for nearly a millennium and remains the spiritual heart of Georgian Christianity. The atmospheric streets lined with traditional stone houses lead to monuments of extraordinary religious and historical significance.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Enter Svetitskhoveli Cathedral, one of the most venerated religious structures in the Caucasus, believed by many Georgians to house the sacred robe of Christ. This magnificent 11th-century masterpiece features remarkable frescoes, intricate stone carvings, and an atmosphere of profound spirituality. The cathedral's architectural grandeur reflects the golden age of medieval Georgian culture.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Climb to Jvari Monastery, perched dramatically on a clifftop overlooking the confluence of the Mtkvari and Aragvi rivers. Dating from the 6th century, this architectural gem represents one of the earliest examples of Georgian ecclesiastical design and offers breathtaking views of Mtskheta below. The monastery's isolated position and ancient stones create an unforgettable atmosphere of contemplation.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
          "to_next_leg": {
