          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Reach Stepantsminda (formerly Kazbegi), the gateway to some of the most spectacular mountain scenery in the entire Caucasus range. This charming highland town sits at 1,740 meters elevation in the shadow of Mount Kazbek, a dormant volcano rising to 5,054 meters that dominates the horizon. The region offers exceptional opportunities for hiking, horseback riding, and experiencing traditional mountain village life.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Hike to Gergeti Trinity Church (Tsminda Sameba), Georgia's most iconic landmark perched on a hilltop at 2,170 meters with Mount Kazbek as its backdrop. This 14th-century stone sanctuary appears to float among the clouds, creating one of the most photographed scenes in the Caucasus. The moderately challenging trail rewards visitors with increasingly dramatic views as elevation increases.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Explore the Truso Valley, a remote glacial landscape dotted with mineral springs, travertine formations, and abandoned stone villages. The valley stretches toward the Russian border through terrain of otherworldly beauty, featuring multicolored rock formations and natural carbonated springs. This off-the-beaten-path adventure showcases the raw wilderness that makes Georgia's mountains so exceptional.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
