            ]
          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Arrive in Sighnaghi, a picturesque hilltop town known as the 'City of Love' for its romantic atmosphere and stunning views over the Alazani Valley. This 18th-century fortified settlement features remarkably preserved defensive walls with 23 towers, each named after nearby villages. Cobblestone streets wind past pastel-colored houses with traditional wooden balconies overlooking endless vineyards below.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Walk the historic town walls that encircle Sighnaghi, stretching over 4 kilometers with accessible towers providing panoramic viewpoints. These impressive fortifications were built by King Erekle II to protect the region's valuable wine-producing communities from invasion. The walls remain among the best-preserved examples of Georgian military architecture from the royal period.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Visit Bodbe Convent, the final resting place of Saint Nino who brought Christianity to Georgia in the 4th century. This active monastery complex features beautifully maintained gardens and a sacred spring believed to possess healing properties. Pilgrims descend a long stairway through cypress groves to reach the spring, creating a contemplative journey through the forested hillside.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            },
            {
              "text": "Experience Kakheti's renowned wine culture at traditional family wineries producing wine using ancient qvevri clay vessel methods. This UNESCO-recognized winemaking technique dates back 8,000 years, making Georgia one of the oldest wine-producing regions on Earth. Sample amber wines, robust reds, and learn about grape varieties found nowhere else in the world.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
