          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Journey to Davit Gareja, an extraordinary 6th-century monastery complex carved into semi-desert hillsides near the Azerbaijani border. Founded by one of the Thirteen Syrian Fathers who spread Christianity throughout the Caucasus, this remote pilgrimage site comprises hundreds of caves, cells, and chapels decorated with medieval frescoes. The stark landscape creates an atmosphere of profound isolation and spiritual contemplation.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Climb to the upper monastery complex for views across the painted desert landscape stretching to the Azerbaijan frontier. Ancient cave cells containing faded but still visible religious paintings dot the cliffsides, testimony to centuries of monastic devotion in this austere environment. Active monks continue to inhabit portions of this remarkable heritage site.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Explore the otherworldly semi-arid terrain surrounding Davit Gareja, characterized by undulating hills, sparse vegetation, and vivid earth tones rarely seen elsewhere in Georgia. This unique ecosystem supports distinctive flora and fauna adapted to the dry conditions. The journey here from Sighnaghi passes through varied landscapes demonstrating the country's remarkable geographic diversity.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
