              "Stalin Childhood House"
            ]
          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Explore Gori, the birthplace of Joseph Stalin and home to the controversial museum documenting his life and legacy. The Stalin Museum complex includes his childhood home preserved under a protective pavilion, his personal railway carriage, and extensive exhibitions of photographs and artifacts. Visitors can examine this complicated historical figure while walking through streets still bearing Soviet-era architecture.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Climb to Gori Fortress, a medieval citadel crowning a rocky hill at the heart of the city with commanding views of the surrounding plains. Archaeological evidence suggests fortifications existed here since before the 1st century BC, making this site witness to millennia of Georgian history. The restored walls and towers provide excellent vantage points for understanding the region's strategic importance.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Visit the Sergi Makalatia Historical and Ethnographic Museum to gain deeper understanding of Georgian cultural traditions and regional history beyond the Stalin narrative. The Cathedral of the Nativity of the Blessed Virgin offers peaceful gardens for contemplation. Gori's central location makes it an ideal base for exploring multiple nearby attractions.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
