          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Arrive in Borjomi, Georgia's famous spa resort town nestled in a forested gorge and renowned worldwide for its naturally carbonated mineral water. The town developed as a fashionable retreat during the 19th century when the Russian imperial family built their summer residence here. Dense pine forests, therapeutic springs, and crisp mountain air continue to attract visitors seeking relaxation and natural wellness.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Stroll through Borjomi Central Park where visitors can sample the famous mineral water directly from the source at no charge. A vintage cable car ascends from the park to panoramic viewpoints overlooking the town and surrounding peaks. The historic bathhouse buildings showcase elegant 19th-century architecture reflecting Borjomi's golden age as a therapeutic destination.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Visit the ornate Romanov Palace, the summer residence of the Russian imperial family featuring distinctive striped red-and-yellow stonework and romantic gardens. The palace grounds offer peaceful walking paths through manicured landscapes. Consider exploring portions of the vast Borjomi-Kharagauli National Park, one of Europe's largest protected areas featuring diverse ecosystems and extensive hiking trails.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
