          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Explore Akhaltsikhe, capital of the Samtskhe-Javakheti region and gateway to Georgia's remarkable southern attractions. The town's history reflects centuries of Georgian and Ottoman influence, creating a unique cultural blend visible in local architecture and traditions. Recently revitalized, the town center provides excellent facilities while maintaining authentic regional character.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Discover the magnificent Rabati Fortress, a stunning medieval castle complex completely restored in recent years to showcase its layered Ottoman and Georgian heritage. The fortress grounds encompass well-maintained gardens, a mosque, a church, and a synagogue, reflecting the region's multicultural history. Climbing the towers rewards visitors with spectacular views of the town and surrounding mountains.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Wander through Rabati's illuminated grounds in the evening when atmospheric lighting transforms the fortress into a magical setting. The complex includes museums documenting local history and traditional crafts. Akhaltsikhe serves as the perfect base for exploring lesser-known destinations including Tmogvi, Khertvisi Fortress, and the remote valleys of southern Georgia.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
