            ]
          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Venture inland from Batumi to discover the mountainous heart of Adjara, a region of forested peaks and traditional villages rarely visited by international travelers. The Lesser Caucasus mountains rise dramatically from the coastal plain, creating landscapes of exceptional beauty. This off-the-beaten-path territory rewards adventurous visitors seeking authentic Georgian mountain culture.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Experience the remarkable Khulo cable car, a small red gondola soaring 350 meters above a deep valley to connect the villages of Khulo and Tago. This spectacular ride offers bird's-eye views of precipitous terrain and traditional highland settlements. The villages themselves provide glimpses of unhurried mountain life far removed from coastal tourist development.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Explore hiking opportunities throughout mountainous Adjara, ranging from day walks to multi-day wilderness treks through pristine highland environments. Numerous guesthouses in remote villages offer authentic hospitality and home-cooked regional specialties. The area remains genuinely undeveloped, providing adventurous travelers with experiences increasingly difficult to find elsewhere in Georgia.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ]
        },
