          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Reach Batumi, Georgia's primary Black Sea resort city, known for its unique blend of historic architecture and striking contemporary buildings earning comparisons to Las Vegas. The beachfront promenade stretches for kilometers along pebbly shores backed by palm trees and modern sculptures. This cosmopolitan city pulses with energy during summer months when visitors from across the region flock to its seaside attractions.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Explore Batumi's charming Old Town, where European-style buildings, narrow lanes, and the historic Orta Jame Mosque reflect the city's multicultural heritage. The region of Adjara maintains distinct cultural traditions with approximately 30 percent Muslim population, distinguishing it from other Georgian regions. Musical fountains, cycling paths, and vibrant nightlife create an atmosphere of celebration.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Hike through the Batumi Botanical Garden, a steep but rewarding trail ascending hillsides covered with exotic plant collections culminating in spectacular Black Sea panoramas. The extensive grounds showcase flora from around the world in a stunning coastal setting. Evening brings the famous dancing fountains to life while the illuminated Boulevard invites leisurely waterfront strolls.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
