          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Alaverdi Cathedral stands alone in the Alazani plain, visible from kilometres away. The first church here was built in the 6th century by an Assyrian monk named Joseph Alaverdeli; the current cathedral was raised by King Kvirike III between 1010 and 1029, reaching 56 metres - for centuries the tallest building in Georgia. But most visitors come for the marani (wine cellar), where monks have been making wine continuously since 1011. The label on every bottle says 'Since 1011'. The cellar holds qvevri from the 8th-10th centuries, with 104 indigenous varieties growing in the monastery vineyards. Tasting with the monks: 30-50€, reservation required. One monk noted: 'Qvevri wines open your heart.' Whether or not that is true, the wine is excellent.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 150
